---
import Layout from '../../layouts/LayoutEN.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Education - Fragrant Signatures" 
  description="Educational programs and courses for creating natural perfumes - School of Natural Perfumery Fragrant Signatures"
  currentPath="/en/education"
>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-gradient-to-br from-botanical-50 via-white to-nature-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-16 max-w-6xl">
      <!-- Hero Section -->
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <div class="mb-8">
          <img 
            src="/images/fw-logo-red.png" 
            alt="Fragrant Signatures Logo"
            class="mx-auto max-w-md h-auto"
          />
        </div>
        
        <!-- Stylized Divider -->
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center mb-8">
          <div class="flex-1 h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-botanical-300 to-transparent"></div>
          <div class="mx-4 w-2 h-2 bg-botanical-500 rounded-full"></div>
          <div class="flex-1 h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-botanical-300 to-transparent"></div>
        </div>
        
        <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-8">
          Education
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-botanical-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
          Discover the world of natural perfumes through our educational programs and courses
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Main Content -->
      <div class="space-y-12">

        <!-- Introduction -->
        <div class="bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12 shadow-xl border border-botanical-100">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-8 text-center">Fragrant Signatures Education</h2>
          
          <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-ink-800 leading-relaxed space-y-6">
            <p>
              Some research results say that when choosing perfumes, we prefer those that fit well with the natural scent of our bodies and harmoniously complete it, thus emphasizing our biological signal.
            </p>
            
            <p>
              Research has also shown that when people apply self-selected fragrances, the effect is rated as more pleasant than when they apply a scent chosen by someone else.
            </p>
            
            <p>
              Knowing that, we can regard self-composed perfumes as extremely exclusive ones, and if we use only natural materials, as top luxury, too.
            </p>
            
            <p>
              If you want to wear a perfume that will cooperate well with your body chemistry, the task of its creation can be best performed by you, your nose and your brain. The self-created natural perfume is an item well worth including into one's personal wellbeing toolbox.
            </p>
            
            <p>
              Would you like to learn how to create such a perfume? If so, you've come to the right place. We are here to ignite your passion for natural perfumes! People wore such perfumes till the end of the 19th century, when they became too expensive and too complicated to produce, so they were replaced by synthetic fragrances.
            </p>
            
            <p class="text-xl font-semibold text-botanical-800 bg-gradient-to-r from-botanical-50 to-nature-50 p-6 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-accent-500">
              The School of Natural Perfumery Fragrant Signatures invites you to join the education.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Topics -->
        <div class="bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12 shadow-xl border border-botanical-100">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-6">Study Topics:</h3>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-800">
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-accent-500 mr-2">•</span>
                The difference between natural and synthetic perfumes
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-accent-500 mr-2">•</span>
                Short history of using natural fragrant materials
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-accent-500 mr-2">•</span>
                Types of fragrance materials (essential oils, absolutes, CO₂ extracts, tinctures, hydrosoles, etc.)
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-accent-500 mr-2">•</span>
                Notes and accords
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-accent-500 mr-2">•</span>
                Scent profiles of 21 materials
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-accent-500 mr-2">•</span>
                Skin chemistry and the effect of scent on emotions
              </li>
            </ul>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-800">
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-accent-500 mr-2">•</span>
                Perfume families and combining scent materials
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-accent-500 mr-2">•</span>
                Different forms of fragrant products (oil-based, alcohol-based and solid perfumes)
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-accent-500 mr-2">•</span>
                Creation and production of a personal alcohol-based perfume
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="text-accent-500 mr-2">•</span>
                Guidelines for further education
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Target Groups -->
        <div class="bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12 shadow-xl border border-botanical-100">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-6">Target Groups:</h3>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-ink-800">
            <p>• Everyone (beginners or professionals) interested in the field of natural perfumery an Fragrant Signatures method.</p>
            <p>• Aromatherapists who want their blends to better suit their clients' personal needs.</p>
            <p>• Sensory researchers who want to sharpen their ability to perceive and recognize scents.</p>
            <p>• Formulators of natural cosmetics who want to improve the scent of their products.</p>
            <p>• Gourmet enthusiasts, sommeliers, winemakers and chefs, because the senses of taste and smell are closely related.</p>
            <p>• All types of therapists, who want to support their work with an adequate fragrant background and thus improve its positive results.</p>
            <p>• Meditation, yoga and mindfulness practitioners.</p>
            <p>• Everyone who is interested in natural scents and wants to get closer to themselves through engaging sense of smell and through creative work.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Modules Overview -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-botanical-50 to-nature-50 rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12 shadow-xl border border-botanical-100">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-6 text-center">Education consists of three modules.</h3>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
            <div class="bg-white/80 rounded-2xl p-6 text-center">
              <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-3">MODULE 1</h4>
              <p class="text-ink-700 text-sm">Basic course in creating natural perfumes</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white/80 rounded-2xl p-6 text-center">
              <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-3">MODULE 2</h4>
              <p class="text-ink-700 text-sm">Advanced course for perfecting the art</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white/80 rounded-2xl p-6 text-center">
              <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-3">MODULE 3</h4>
              <p class="text-ink-700 text-sm">Creating perfumes for other people</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- MODULE 1 -->
        <div class="bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12 shadow-xl border border-botanical-100">
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-8 text-center">Module 1</h3>
          
          <div class="space-y-8">
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-botanical-700 mb-4">Programme & Schedule:</h4>
              <p class="text-ink-800 mb-4">
                Programme is divided into six sessions, including an introductory session, followed by four weekends of practice (one per month), and a follow-up session.
              </p>
              <p class="text-ink-800 mb-4">
                After each weekend of practice, students are given tasks that they should master by the next meeting.
              </p>
              <p class="text-ink-800">
                In addition, students will have to complete a final assignment prior to the follow-up session.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div class="bg-botanical-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-3">Introductory Meeting (2-3 hours)</h5>
                <p class="text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  Before the start of the education, at the introductory meeting, students will receive all the necessary instructions and will be shown how to prepare their perfumers' palettes.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-nature-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-nature-800 mb-3">First Weekend</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>• Introduction</li>
                  <li>• Fragrant Materials</li>
                  <li>• Sourcing, Selecting and Storing Fragrant Materials</li>
                  <li>• Working with Fragrant Materials</li>
                  <li>• How to Evaluate Scents</li>
                  <li>• Notes in Perfumery</li>
                  <li>• Base Notes Evaluation</li>
                  <li>• Discussion: Individual Impressions and Preferences</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-accent-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-accent-800 mb-3">Second Weekend</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>• Classification by Scent Groups</li>
                  <li>• Accords' Formulation</li>
                  <li>• Evaluation of Middle Notes</li>
                  <li>• Discussion: Impressions and Personal Preferences</li>
                  <li>• Perfume Formulation Method by J. Carles</li>
                  <li>• Base Accord Creation</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-botanical-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-3">Third Weekend</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>• Discussion: Experience of Creating the Base Accord / Olfactory Impression</li>
                  <li>• Skin Chemistry</li>
                  <li>• Perfume Evolution</li>
                  <li>• Top Notes Evaluation</li>
                  <li>• Creating a Middle Accord</li>
                  <li>• First Impressions of the Middle Accord</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-nature-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-nature-800 mb-3">Fourth Weekend</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>• Discussion: Experience of Creating the Top Accord / Olfactory Impression</li>
                  <li>• Filling in the Perfume Formula Form</li>
                  <li>• Balancing Accords – Trials and Selection</li>
                  <li>• Perfume Creation</li>
                  <li>• Perfumes' Classification by Concentration</li>
                  <li>• On Possible Post Festum Interventions</li>
                  <li>• Questions and Concluding Discussion</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-accent-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-accent-800 mb-3">Follow-up Meeting</h5>
                <p class="text-ink-700 text-sm font-semibold mb-2">Before this meeting, a final assignment should be handed in, which consists of:</p>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>1. completed questionnaire</li>
                  <li>2. a paper on the given topic</li>
                  <li>3. completed perfume evaluation form</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="text-ink-700 text-sm mt-3">Follow-up meeting consists of:</p>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>• discussion about the creative process carried out</li>
                  <li>• guidelines for further work</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-botanical-50 to-nature-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
              <h5 class="font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-4">Details About the Education</h5>
              <div class="space-y-4 text-ink-800 text-sm">
                <p>• Before the start of the education each student will receive their personal kit. There will be 21 fragrant materials for the perfumer's palette, plus few useful bonus items in it. During the introductory meeting, students will get instructions on how to prepare palettes.</p>
                <p>• It is necessary to purchase the manual Fragrant Signatures. You can order it here. By entering AROMATERAPIJA20 into Discount Code box, you will get 20% discount on the price of the manual.</p>
                <p>• Everyone should prepare 15 (10 ml) dark bottles with pipettes / caps, labels, a sufficient amount of blotters, and a thick notebook for recording their impressions, thoughts, ideas…</p>
                <p>• Classes are usually held on Saturdays and Sundays from 4.00 pm to 7.30 pm CET. (During the introductory meeting we can adjust the hourly rate, to better suit everyone.)</p>
                <p>• The complete education takes place interactively (without pre-recorded videos) and with the constant engagement of the teacher. This is why, despite the online form, the education is still very personal and enables the formation of close contact within the group. To acquire this type of knowledge, working in a group is of crucial importance, because a lot is learned by listening to the impressions and opinions of other participants (a-ha moments!).</p>
                <p>• The created perfume is unique, and represents one's personal, specific fragrant signature. Its formulation was influenced by creator's physical, mental, psychological, and spiritual needs, which shape each person's olfactory preferences. You can wear it as your only & forever perfume that will accompany you at every step, and in all life situations. Or you can modify it over time and adapt it to your changing needs. And, of course, you can create a lot of other perfumes whenever you decide so. This education prepares you to do that.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div class="bg-white/80 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-botanical-200">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-4">Education includes:</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>• working in a small group and in real time</li>
                  <li>• interactivity and tasks for individual work at home</li>
                  <li>• careful mentoring throughout the entire perfume making process</li>
                  <li>• certificate of completed education</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-white/80 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-botanical-200">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-4">Details:</h5>
                <div class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <p><strong>Duration:</strong> Live online: 38 teaching hours. Individual work at home: minimum 30 hours.</p>
                  <p><strong>Location:</strong> online event via ZOOM</p>
                  <p><strong>Language:</strong> English</p>
                  <p><strong>Group size:</strong> In order to ensure the quality of work, we can accept a maximum of 10 people in a group. When the places are taken, we will put you on the waiting list, just in case a place becomes available at the last minute. Thank you for your understanding!</p>
                  <p><strong>Price:</strong> 900,00 euros</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-accent-50 p-6 rounded-2xl text-center">
              <h5 class="font-bold text-accent-800 mb-3">Enrollment:</h5>
              <p class="text-ink-800 font-semibold">+385 91 788 6783</p>
              <p class="text-ink-700 text-sm mt-2">The invitation to enroll in the education is sent on average twice a year, and the education is held when a group of interested people is formed.</p>
              <p class="text-ink-700 text-sm mt-2 font-semibold">Information and registration: +385 91 788 6783</p>
              <p class="text-ink-700 text-sm mt-2">Note: After completing Module 1 participants are trained to create alcohol perfumes and can finish their education at this level.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- MODULE 2 -->
        <div class="bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12 shadow-xl border border-botanical-100">
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-8 text-center">Module 2</h3>
          
          <div class="space-y-8">
            <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-nature-50 to-botanical-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
              <p class="text-ink-800 text-lg">
                This module is intended for those persistent and curious who want to learn further, improve their art of composing natural perfumes, and refine their creations.
              </p>
              <p class="text-ink-800 mt-4">
                Those who already have experience in the creation of natural perfumes do not have to pre-complete Module 1, but they will need to demonstrate (during the introductory interview) that they possess the knowledge required for the Module 2 level of education.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-botanical-50 to-nature-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
              <h5 class="font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-4">Details about the Education</h5>
              <div class="space-y-4 text-ink-800 text-sm">
                <p>• Before the start of the education, each student will be sent their personal kit. There will be 21 fragrant materials for the perfumer's palette and a few useful items as a surprise in it. During the introductory meeting, students will receive instructions on how to prepare palettes.</p>
                <p>• Everyone should also prepare 40 vials with pipettes / caps, labels, a sufficient amount of blotters, and a thick notebook for recording their impressions, thoughts, ideas….</p>
                <p>• The complete education is conducted interactively, without prerecorded videos, in real time and with the constant support of the teacher and the administrator. This is why, despite the online form, the education is still very personal and enables the formation of close contact within the group. To acquire this type of knowledge, working in a group is of crucial importance, because a lot is learned by listening to the impressions and opinions of other participants (aha moments!)</p>
                <p>• During this module you get to know several methods of perfume creation, and you choose the formulation method that you think will best suit your chosen perfume plan. In the final part, during the follow-up meeting, you can discuss with the mentor your impressions and possible dilemmas regarding the creation process you went through.</p>
                <p class="font-semibold">Note: In order to be able to work with a larger amount of fragrant components, students are expected to have at hand Module 1 palette materials.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-botanical-700 mb-4">Programme & Schedule:</h4>
              
              <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                <div class="bg-botanical-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                  <h5 class="font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-3">First Session</h5>
                  <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                    <li>• Discussion about previous experiences in creating natural perfumes</li>
                    <li>• Evaluation of the first group of fragrant materials in the palette</li>
                    <li>• First impressions, discussion</li>
                    <li>• Theory: work with „difficult" materials, different dilutions, other forms of perfumes</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-nature-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                  <h5 class="font-bold text-nature-800 mb-3">Second Session</h5>
                  <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                    <li>• Impressions after getting to know the first group of materials in detail</li>
                    <li>• Evaluation of the next group of fragrant materials</li>
                    <li>• Impressions, discussion</li>
                    <li>• Theory: precise measurement (working with scales)</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-accent-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                  <h5 class="font-bold text-accent-800 mb-3">Third Session</h5>
                  <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                    <li>• Discussion after a detailed introduction to the second group of materials</li>
                    <li>• Evaluation of the last group of fragrant materials</li>
                    <li>• Olfactory impressions, discussion</li>
                    <li>• Theory: bases / doppelgangers</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-botanical-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                  <h5 class="font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-3">Fourth Session</h5>
                  <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                    <li>• Impressions about the last group of fragrant materials</li>
                    <li>• Base creation experience</li>
                    <li>• Theory: different approaches to perfume creation</li>
                    <li>• The decision on the method of creating the perfume (EdT)</li>
                    <li>• Practical work: creating a perfume using the chosen method</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="bg-accent-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                  <h5 class="font-bold text-accent-800 mb-3">Follow-up Meeting</h5>
                  <p class="text-ink-700 text-sm font-semibold mb-2">Before this meeting the participants should submit:</p>
                  <ul class="space-y-1 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                    <li>1. a paper on the given topic</li>
                    <li>2. completed perfume evaluation form</li>
                  </ul>
                  <p class="text-ink-700 text-sm mt-3">Follow-up meeting consists of:</p>
                  <ul class="space-y-1 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                    <li>• Discussion about the applied methods of creation and individual reports on the created perfumes</li>
                    <li>• Suggestions for further work: maintaining creative competence, care for personal ecological footprint, sustainability, etc.</li>
                    <li>• Short individual interviews with the mentor.</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div class="bg-white/80 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-botanical-200">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-4">Education includes:</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <li>• working in a small group and in real time</li>
                  <li>• interactivity and tasks for individual work at home</li>
                  <li>• careful mentoring throughout the entire perfume making process</li>
                  <li>• certificate of completed education</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-white/80 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-botanical-200">
                <h5 class="font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-4">Details:</h5>
                <div class="space-y-2 text-ink-700 text-sm">
                  <p><strong>Duration:</strong> Live online: 22 teaching hours. Individual work at home: minimum 25 hours.</p>
                  <p><strong>Language:</strong> English</p>
                  <p><strong>Location:</strong> online event via ZOOM</p>
                  <p><strong>Price:</strong> 900,00 €</p>
                  <p><strong>Group size:</strong> In order to enable quality work, we can take a maximum of 8 people in a group. When the seats are taken, we will put you on the waiting list, just in case a place becomes available at the last minute. Thank you in advance for your understanding!</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-accent-50 p-6 rounded-2xl text-center">
              <h5 class="font-bold text-accent-800 mb-3">Enrollment:</h5>
              <p class="text-ink-800 font-semibold">aromaterapija.info</p>
              <p class="text-ink-800 font-semibold">+385 91 788 678</p>
              <p class="text-ink-700 text-sm mt-2">Enrollment is announced twice a year. The education is held when a group of interested parties is formed.</p>
              <p class="text-ink-700 text-sm mt-2">Information and Registration: aromaterapija.info +385 91 788 678</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- MODULE 3 -->
        <div class="bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12 shadow-xl border border-botanical-100">
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-8 text-center">Module 3</h3>
          
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-nature-50 to-botanical-50 p-6 rounded-2xl text-center">
            <p class="text-ink-800 text-lg">
              There is a possibility to organize Module 3 for those who want to learn how to create natural perfumes for other people.
            </p>
            <p class="text-ink-800 mt-4">
              This module is organized by agreement, when a group of interested parties is formed. The method and details of this part of the education are agreed upon at the scheduled meeting.
            </p>
            <p class="text-ink-800 mt-4 font-semibold">
              Note: For any additional questions, please use the contact form.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Author and Testimonials -->
        <div class="bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12 shadow-xl border border-botanical-100">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-6 text-center">Copyright:</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-800 text-center text-lg">
            The author of <a href="https://aromaterapija.info/skola-kreiranja-prirodnih-parfema/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-botanical-600 hover:text-botanical-800 underline font-medium transition-colors duration-300">Fragrant Signatures education</a> is Slobodanka Poštić.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Testimonials -->
        <div class="bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12 shadow-xl border border-botanical-100">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-botanical-800 mb-8 text-center">Impressions of former students:</h3>
          
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="bg-botanical-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
              <p class="text-ink-800 italic">
                "My knowledge of perfumes was in the range of perfume products in the store – you smell, you buy; and the question of colleagues: what perfume do you use! That I can put together the most beautiful scents, scents that are dear to me, it's something I didn't know exist."
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-nature-50 p-6 rounded-2xl">
              <p class="text-ink-800 italic">
